g.title: EleanorRank4Convo3 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank4Convo3 begins.

g.title: j1748649499
g.text: I think I’ve done it. I broke through. I made contact.

g.title: j3707949674
g.text: Are you there? Please be there.

g.title: j3562143527
g.text: Am I going to have to do this over telepathy? Oh God. Please not now.

g.title: j3572543739
g.text: Eleanor, slow down. What’s going on?

g.title: j3426972941
g.text: [Ignore.]

g.title: j654081298
g.text: Check boolean EleanorSister

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j310220515
g.text: The other me. The one who became a nun. I’ve been trying to contact her.

g.title: j654081298->j310220515
g.text: true

g.title: j1546619229
g.text: Ever since you appeared, a question has been pestering me. A question I believe I might've just answered. And dear Sol I don't know what I've done.

g.title: j654081298->j1546619229
g.text: false

g.title: j3596411623
g.text: I just did it.

g.title: j1087024683
g.text: Start at the beginning. I don't know what you're talking about. What question?

g.title: j2757542933
g.text: Of course it was never going to work so long as I stayed in this world. I’m already the ‘me’ of this world. I had to go through the roaring whiteness. The blackstar fugue. The leechbone gulf. That’s how you get to the other sides. The maybes and the could-have-beens.

g.title: j2826326797
g.text: You! The question of bloody You. You exist not once but twice.

g.title: j1741335716
g.text: The Void! I saw the Void!

g.title: j3999770098
g.text: And if you could exist in another world, as another version of yourself, why couldn't I?

g.title: j4103098519
g.text: Are you... sure you didn't get into Lettie's special stash?

g.title: j2842773701
g.text: That shouldn’t be possible, Eleanor. Nobody enters the Void until Albrecht Entrati does it. That’s a long way into the future from where we are now.

g.title: j1667319004
g.text: Somewhere out there in the now-confirmed-to-exist vast possible universes was that version of myself that I always wondered if I should become.

g.title: j1974630145
g.text: Drifter dear, I admire your ability to use humour as a coping mechanism, but right now I am entirely serious.

g.title: j1915035077
g.text: I went in with my mind, not my body. That’s the difference.

g.title: j3686890258
g.text: The one who turned away from the world to become a nun.

g.title: j2787638160
g.text: I did what I set out to do.

g.title: j1131717531
g.text: Ow headache ow ow ow

g.title: j61510342
g.text: An apostle of Lua sat on a mountaintop somewhere, incense clouds flowering around her.

g.title: j3603219789
g.text: I not only saw the Void, I entered it.

g.title: j3014708669
g.text: Check boolean EleanorIndifference2

g.title: j1003914446
g.text: I've been trying to contact her. Trying to reach through the Void to find her.

g.title: j3474531682
g.text: If you really did enter the Void, I cannot tell you how much danger you were putting yourself in. You know what’s out there, and you still just dove into it?

g.title: j3014708669->j3474531682
g.text: true

g.title: j2567733963
g.text: Are you insane?!

g.title: j3014708669->j2567733963
g.text: true

g.title: j3014708669->j2567733963
g.text: false

g.title: j1069464196
g.text: What did you see? What happened?

g.title: j3014708669->j1069464196
g.text: false

g.title: j3212129121
g.text: Boolean EleanorSister is now true.

g.title: j2472551231
g.text: That’s how I got into the Void in the first place. Through that memory. The horror was just smoke and through the smoke was a GATE. If I hadn’t been so frightened I would have seen it clearly the first time around.

g.title: j1033998371
g.text: Not even a little bit.

g.title: j3186668364
g.text: There’s a feeling there isn’t a word for. You look out on the world and you just KNOW, that all the ordinariness - buildings, cars, people, jobs, work, routine - is just a thin crust over a bottomless horror, and if people ever realized it they’d start screaming and never stop.

g.title: j1948348822
g.text: Oh no.

g.title: j1884203746
g.text: And...?

g.title: j594349521
g.text: This was a mistake. It took Rusalka. It came damn close to taking Albrecht. It could easily take you too.

g.title: j3951306673
g.text: Just listen. Please. And try to understand.

g.title: j2643692192
g.text: I fell through the crust.

g.title: j2891540314
g.text: It tried. I felt it. I knew it was curious, reaching for me.

g.title: j4269642011
g.text: So out of infinities of possible worlds, you just happened to home in on the right one?

g.title: j718146887
g.text: Eleanor, the Indifference can look like whatever it wants. It looked like Albrecht when he first encountered it.

g.title: j3723520700
g.text: It wasn’t emptiness. I could have borne that. It went on and on forever, but it wasn’t just cold space. There was something in there with me.

g.title: j1147696079
g.text: It’s okay that you’re not convinced. I know this sounds insane. Just hear me out, okay?

g.title: j2645095451
g.text: I think maybe it sensed what you wanted and took on the form you were hoping to see.

g.title: j639434477
g.text: Boolean EleanorIndifference2 is now true.

g.title: j31664789
g.text: I’ll make a deal with you.

g.title: j2054991508
g.text: First you let me finish telling you what happened.

g.title: j2743533167
g.text: Once I’m done, you can make your own mind up about whether it was the Indifference messing with me or not. I promise I’ll take you seriously.

g.title: j504988741
g.text: Deal?

g.title: j4279338403
g.text: Deal.

g.title: j1489393238
g.text: I can't believe you did this. Never do that again, Eleanor! I CAN'T LOSE YOU TO THAT THING!

g.title: j2605015932
g.text: So like I was saying. I found her.

g.title: j2726655618
g.text: Excuse me?

g.title: j389500478
g.text: I could feel the Indifference watching. I could feel it make a face like one of those dried-out desert mummies as it reached out for me. I reached out for her, and she pulled me through.

g.title: j4025609458
g.text: I'm not sure what to say. I'm a bit concerned, because you sound so upset, but I didn't realise you cared quite so much.

g.title: j887290170
g.text: She was sitting in the Lotus position in some kind of open-air shrine, next to a pit full of embers. It was nighttime. The moon was dim, ghosting through scrolling clouds.

g.title: j2127839202
g.text: I'm all right. Please don't worry about me.

g.title: j1117132410
g.text: She put a finger to her lips.

g.title: j3136398766
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j1852168884
g.text: For a second I could feel that giant hand still groping for me. Then it recoiled, like a guillotine had come down on one of its fingers.

g.title: j914383264
g.text: I can't promise anything, but I'll try not to scare you again.

g.title: j3825933646
g.text: Grass whispered. Crickets sang. We were alone.

g.title: j538028019
g.text: Fine... just... Tell me what happened.

g.title: j2016450503
g.text: I can't be a party to this. [End.]

g.title: j667928400
g.text: This is all sounding horribly familiar. And then?

g.title: j3153525120
g.text: We sat across the fire-pit from each other. She didn’t speak, but she let me look into her mind, soft and sisterly.

g.title: j2778286317
g.text: She was so happy, so perfectly content. A woman in the place that was right for her. Callused feet, clear eyes. Breathing the fire and drinking the moon.

g.title: j1021888304
g.text: So you felt that WOULD have been the right choice for you?

g.title: j2290931050
g.text: Did you feel tempted to stay?

g.title: j681868714
g.text: No! Just the opposite!

g.title: j2353922950
g.text: I didn’t need to take that path, because she already had. Don’t you see? I’m free now. I never need to wonder ‘what if’ because there already IS a Sister Eleanor. She’s got my back. Am I making sense?

g.title: j2452088649
g.text: Kind of? All I want to know is, did it help?

g.title: j713556842
g.text: Oh yeah. I’ve never been more certain of what to do next.

g.title: j929683391
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j1368351291
g.text: I’m going to take the life she freed me up to live, and live it to the hilt.
